12:33.794 --> 12:36.964
♪ AND I WANT EVERYONE TO SEE ♪

12:37.047 --> 12:40.259
♪ HEY, LOOK AT ME. ♪

12:40.342 --> 12:41.177
AWESOME.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.303
NO, NO, KEEP PLAYING.

12:42.386 --> 12:44.930
THAT'S THE BEST SONG
I'VE EVER HEARD, HANDS DOWN.

12:45.014 --> 12:47.850
[SCOFFS] WE'RE IN REHEARSAL,
BESSIE, BAND MEMBERS ONLY.

12:47.933 --> 12:49.435
YOU GUYS HAVE A BAND?

12:49.518 --> 12:52.146
DUH, WE'RE THE PRETTY,
PRETTY PRINCESSES.

12:52.229 --> 12:54.273
I SING- AGAIN, DUH.

12:54.356 --> 12:56.275
GWEN'S ON GUITAR.

12:56.358 --> 12:58.027
AND PENNY ROCKS THE TRIANGLE.

12:58.110 --> 13:01.238
ITS NAME IS THE SAME
AS ITS SHAPE.

13:01.322 --> 13:04.408
{\an3}WE'RE PLAYING THE SAN FRANCISCO
SUMMER CONCERT SERIES.

13:04.492 --> 13:07.995
THE SAN FRANCISCO SUMMER CONCERT
SERIES, THAT'S HUGE.

13:08.078 --> 13:10.289
{\an3}WHAT'S MY PART,
WHAT AM I GONNA PLAY?

13:10.372 --> 13:11.665
{\an3}WE ALREADY HAVE
A SINGER, "MESSY."

13:11.749 --> 13:12.374
{\an3}AND BESIDES, YOU DON'T
PLAY AN INSTRUMENT.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.709
TOO BAD, SO SAD. [SCOFFS]

13:13.792 --> 13:17.546
MY BODY IS AN INSTRUMENT,
I'M A ONE-MAN BAND.

13:17.630 --> 13:18.255
[IMITATING MOUTH HARP]

13:18.339 --> 13:19.381
[FARTING NOISES]

13:19.465 --> 13:21.550
[BLOWING RASPBERRY]

13:21.634 --> 13:22.760
{\an5}GROSS.

13:21.634 --> 13:22.760
[FEEDBACK WHINES]

13:22.843 --> 13:25.346
YOU TOTALLY RUIN
THE ACOUSTICS IN THIS ROOM.

13:25.429 --> 13:26.555
WE'RE OUT OF HERE,
GREAT, THANKS, BYE.

13:26.639 --> 13:30.351
BUT I WANT TO ROCK SO HARD.

13:31.060 --> 13:32.394
I NEED TO BORROW YOUR TUBA.

13:32.478 --> 13:34.146
BUT I NEED TO PRACTICE.

13:34.230 --> 13:35.981
{\an3}BENJAMIN, THIS IS OFFICIAL
HONEYBEE BUSINESS.

13:36.065 --> 13:37.733
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TRUST ME.

13:37.816 --> 13:39.401
HERE, PRACTICE ON HAPPY.

13:39.485 --> 13:41.237
HOW DO YOU PLAY A DOG?

13:41.320 --> 13:42.863
[GROWLS]

13:42.947 --> 13:46.325
[TUBA PLAYING]

13:46.408 --> 13:48.285
♪ TWINKLE, TWINKLE,
LITTLE STAR ♪

13:48.369 --> 13:50.579
♪ HOW I WONDER... ♪

13:50.663 --> 13:52.164
OOH, UH...

13:52.248 --> 13:53.290
♪ L-M-N-O-P ♪

13:53.374 --> 13:56.210
TUBA BREAK.

14:00.673 --> 14:01.590
[TUBA TOOTS]

14:01.674 --> 14:04.260
[SIGHS]

14:04.343 --> 14:06.804
REALLY, YOU DO?

14:06.887 --> 14:07.763
[♪...]

14:07.846 --> 14:09.348
[BESSIE CLEARS THROAT] MAESTRO.

14:09.431 --> 14:13.769
[PLAYS POORLY]

14:15.938 --> 14:20.943
["BEETHOVEN'S FIFTH" PLAYS...]

14:23.362 --> 14:24.905
Bessie: WHO AM I KIDDING, ROCKY?

14:24.989 --> 14:27.491
I'LL NEVER GET TO PLAY WITH
THE GREATEST BAND OF ALL TIME.

14:27.575 --> 14:29.118
{\an3}WELL, EVERYONE WISHES THEY COULD
PLAY WITH THE RAMONES.

14:29.201 --> 14:32.997
HUH? NO, I'M TALKING ABOUT
THE PRETTY, PRETTY PRINCESSES.

14:33.080 --> 14:35.124
AH, THEY PLAY
THE BEST SONG EVER.

14:35.207 --> 14:37.376
{\an1}HAVE YOU HEARD IT, "RUNNING WITH
THE RAINBOW UNICORN"?

14:37.459 --> 14:39.503
IT'S AN INSTANT CLASSIC.

14:39.587 --> 14:40.462
{\an1}♪ I'M A PRETTY,
PRETTY PRINCESS ♪

14:40.546 --> 14:44.425
♪ IT'S A FULL-TIME GIG ♪

14:44.508 --> 14:47.761
[SIGHS] AH, FORGET IT,
I'M NO MUSICIAN.

14:47.845 --> 14:49.388
HEY, I FEEL YOU, B.

14:49.471 --> 14:51.348
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT THEY CALL
SOMEONE WHO'S NO MUSICIAN?

14:51.432 --> 14:51.765
WHAT?

14:51.849 --> 14:53.851
A DRUMMER.

14:58.230 --> 14:59.648
WICKED, YOU DESTROYED, ROCKS.

14:59.732 --> 15:02.610
CHECK IT,
I'M NOT EVEN A DRUMMER.

15:02.693 --> 15:03.902
I PLAY BASS.

15:03.986 --> 15:05.154
I TOLD YOU,<i> ANYONE</i> CAN DO THIS.

15:05.237 --> 15:06.864
[GASPS] ARE YOU SURE IT'S OK?

15:06.947 --> 15:09.867
SURE, OUR DRUMMER'S
AT SPACE CAMP.

15:16.749 --> 15:20.294
[GRUNTING]

15:20.377 --> 15:22.171
IT'S LIKE LIGHTNING
RUNNING THROUGH MY STICKS.

15:22.254 --> 15:25.382
[GRUNTING]

15:25.466 --> 15:28.177
[GRUNTING RAPIDLY]

15:28.260 --> 15:29.595
CHECK IT OUT, PHIL COLLINS.

15:29.678 --> 15:31.055
[IMITATES CYMBAL]

15:32.389 --> 15:34.850
WHAT?

15:34.933 --> 15:36.435
WHERE DID I GO?

15:36.518 --> 15:37.853
WOW.

15:37.936 --> 15:40.522
{\an3}SORRY, DUDE, I, UM,
JUST GOT LOST IN THE MOMENT.

15:40.606 --> 15:43.609
UH... THAT WAS GREAT, B.

15:43.692 --> 15:45.778
{\an1}YOU DEFINITELY GOT THE DRIVE,
BUT NOW YOU NEED THE CHOPS.

15:45.861 --> 15:48.822
PAY CLOSE ATTENTION,
'CAUSE I'M ABOUT TO SCHOOL YOU.

15:48.906 --> 15:49.156
[♪...]

15:49.239 --> 15:51.033
[GASPS]

16:36.578 --> 16:38.247
SHE ROCKS PRETTY HARD, HUH?

16:38.330 --> 16:40.416
[GRUNTS] YEAH, FOR A CHICK.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.918
{\an3}WE DO NEED A NEW DRUMMER,
WHY NOT BETSY?

16:43.001 --> 16:43.544
UM, IT'S BESSIE.

16:43.627 --> 16:45.713
[GRUNTS] SHE'S LIKE 4'2".

16:45.796 --> 16:47.214
I COULD WEAR MY MOON BOOTS.

16:47.297 --> 16:48.716
HEY, SHE CAN'T BE WORSE THAN
GARY, BONZO OR TOAD.

16:48.799 --> 16:52.720
YEAH, AND GET THIS, SHE'S HERE.

16:52.803 --> 16:54.972
[GRUNTS] THAT'S TRUE.

16:55.055 --> 16:57.182
SHE <i> IS</i> HERE, NOT AT SPACE CAMP.

16:57.266 --> 16:57.891
SO WHAT DO YOU SAY, B?

16:57.975 --> 17:00.102
YOU WANT TO BE AN INTEGRITONE?

17:00.185 --> 17:01.478
DO YOU GUYS
HAVE A SMOKE MACHINE?

17:01.562 --> 17:02.604
WE CAN RENT ONE.

17:02.688 --> 17:03.230
YES!

17:03.313 --> 17:04.356
BRING IT IN, EVERYBODY.

17:04.440 --> 17:07.108
I JUST WANT YOU GUYS TO KNOW
I WON'T LET YOU DOWN.

17:07.192 --> 17:07.943
I'M GONNA BE THE BEST DRUMMER
YOU EVER HAD.

17:08.026 --> 17:11.280
{\an3}[GRUNTS] COOL,
MAYBE LET GO NOW?

17:13.240 --> 17:16.242
WOW, OMINOUS.

17:19.704 --> 17:20.789
GOOD MORNING,
FELLOW INTEGRITONE.

17:20.873 --> 17:22.915
I BROUGHT YOU SOME CROISSANTS.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.002
ROCKS, YOU'RE NOT EVEN DRESSED?

17:25.085 --> 17:27.378
B., IT'S 6:30.

17:27.463 --> 17:28.589
{\an1}MUSICIANS DON'T GET UP
TILL AT LEAST, LIKE, 4:00.

17:28.672 --> 17:31.341
[LAUGHS] EXCUSE ME.

17:31.425 --> 17:33.510
BUT WHEN PHIL COLLINS
WAS STILL IN GENESIS

17:33.594 --> 17:35.345
HE WOULD GET UP
AT 6:00 EVERY MORNING

17:35.429 --> 17:37.097
JUST TO DO HAND CALISTHENICS,
RIGHT, FINGER?

17:37.181 --> 17:39.016
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

17:39.099 --> 17:41.310
FIVE, GO, FINGER,
SIX, SEVEN, GO, FINGER

17:41.393 --> 17:43.437
EIGHT, NINE, GO, FINGER.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.981
OH, MY EYES, THE LIGHT.

17:46.064 --> 17:49.902
[GROANS] FIVE MORE MINUTES,
MOM, PLEASE?

17:49.985 --> 17:53.405
HOW 'BOUT WE JUST CATCH UP WITH
YOU LATER AT THE CAFE, B., COOL?

17:53.489 --> 17:56.074
OH, NO, NO, SURE, I, YOU KNOW,
I GOT A LOT OF IMPORTANT STUFF

17:56.158 --> 17:59.953
{\an3}I GOTTA DO BEFORE WE PRACTICE,
LIKE, UM... PRACTICE.

18:00.037 --> 18:01.038
SOLID, WE'LL SEE YOU THEN.

18:01.121 --> 18:02.039
WHEN'S "THEN"?

18:02.122 --> 18:03.332
LATER, THEN.

18:05.125 --> 18:08.504
{\an3}[BOY GRUNTS] MAN,
GOTTA FINISH THIS SONG.

18:08.587 --> 18:11.673
"SHE PLUNGES INTO MY SOUL
LIKE AN ANCHOR IN THE..."

18:11.757 --> 18:12.841
{\an1}BOAT?

18:12.925 --> 18:15.552
AH, IT'LL COME TO US,
YOU CAN'T RUSH THESE THINGS.

18:15.636 --> 18:18.514
{\an3}OH, I KNOW, HOW ABOUT SOMETHING
ABOUT RAINBOWS OR UNICORNS?

18:18.597 --> 18:20.849
"LIKE AN ANCHOR IN THE RAINBOW"?

18:20.933 --> 18:24.645
{\an5}I DON'T THINK WE NEED ANY
RAINBOWS OR UNICORNS IN
OUR LYRICS, BETSY.

18:24.728 --> 18:25.938
YEAH, I HEAR YOU, I GET IT.

18:26.021 --> 18:27.731
WELL, HOW 'BOUT SOMETHING,
UM, ABOUT, UM

18:27.815 --> 18:30.025
MULTICOLORED SPECTRUMS OF LIGHT

18:30.108 --> 18:31.026
OR, UH, MYSTICAL,
ONE-HORNED BEASTS

18:31.109 --> 18:33.028
THAT ONLY APPEAR TO YOU
IN YOUR DREAMS?

18:33.111 --> 18:35.823
HEY, ONE-HORNED BEASTS
SOUND COOL.

18:35.906 --> 18:38.367
DUDE, IT'S A UNICORN.

18:38.450 --> 18:40.869
{\an3}HEY, BESSIE,
I GOT A KILLER IDEA.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.372
{\an3}WHY DON'T YOU GO
HANG POSTERS FOR OUR GIG?

18:43.455 --> 18:47.793
{\an5}I'M SENDING YOU ON
A ROCK-N-ROLL MISSION,
ARE YOU UP TO IT?

18:53.131 --> 18:56.385
WOW, GLITTER <i> AND</i> SPARKLES?

18:56.468 --> 18:59.388
HMM...

18:59.471 --> 19:01.014
KNOCK-KNOCK, WHO'S THERE?

19:01.098 --> 19:02.224
THE INTEGRITONES.

19:02.307 --> 19:03.600
THE INTEGRITONES, WHO?

19:03.684 --> 19:07.187
THE INTEGRITONES HAVE JUST GOT
AN AWESOME VAN MAKEOVER.

19:09.314 --> 19:13.026
ROCKS, YOU GOTTA CHECK THIS OUT,
IT EVEN SMELLS LIKE CHERRIES.

19:13.110 --> 19:15.237
THIS SO NOT COOL, MAN.

19:15.320 --> 19:18.198
{\an1}SHE BESMIRCHED THE VAN, ROCKS,
THE VAN IS OUR WHOLE THING.

19:18.282 --> 19:20.659
{\an5}I KNOW, GUYS, I KNOW.

19:18.282 --> 19:20.659
[BESSIE HUMS]

19:20.742 --> 19:23.704
LOOK, WE JUST GOTTA GET THROUGH
THIS GIG AND THEN...

19:23.787 --> 19:25.581
AND THEN I'LL TELL HER
SHE'S OUT OF THE BAND.

19:25.664 --> 19:26.498
{\an3}[HUMMING]

19:26.582 --> 19:32.296
[CHEERING...]

19:32.379 --> 19:34.173
{\an5}♪ IT'S SAID OF A BILLIONAIRE,
HOW WOULD IT FEEL TO BE
A TRILLIONAIRE? ♪

19:37.509 --> 19:38.969
♪ YEAH ♪

19:39.052 --> 19:41.638
♪ ...THEY SING THIS SONG,
DOO-DAH, DOO-DAH ♪

19:41.722 --> 19:42.514
♪ THE CAMPTOWN RACETRACK... ♪

19:42.598 --> 19:44.433
{\an3}WHOA.

19:44.516 --> 19:47.019
HEY, GUYS, I JUST WANTED TO
TELL YOU TO HAVE A GREAT SHOW.

19:47.102 --> 19:49.271
I KNOW YOU WILL BECAUSE
WHO DOESN'T LIKE SONGS ABOUT...

19:49.354 --> 19:53.400
{\an6}UM, "MESSY," SORRY,
BUT BACKSTAGE IS ONLY FOR
BANDS AND THEIR GROUPIES

19:53.483 --> 19:56.820
{\an6}WELL-WISHERS,
CONCERT VOLUNTEERS,
FOOD DELIVERY GUYS AND JANITORS.

19:56.904 --> 19:58.238
UM, YOU GUYS?

19:58.322 --> 20:00.449
I THINK THERE ARE, LIKE,
30 PEOPLE OUT THERE.

20:00.532 --> 20:01.617
TRY 3,000.

20:01.700 --> 20:02.659
[GROANS]

20:02.743 --> 20:04.620
{\an3}[GASPS]

20:04.703 --> 20:05.579
{\an3}HI, ROCKY.

20:05.662 --> 20:07.497
{\an1}HEY.

20:07.581 --> 20:08.582
B., THE GUYS ARE
LOOKING FOR YOU.

20:08.665 --> 20:12.085
{\an1}WE'RE ON RIGHT AFTER
THE PRETTY, PRETTY PRINCESSES.

20:12.169 --> 20:13.253
I HEAR YOU MAN.

20:13.337 --> 20:14.630
GOOD LUCK, YOU GUYS.

20:14.713 --> 20:17.466
"MESSY" IN A BAND?

20:17.549 --> 20:18.634
WITH ROCKY?

20:18.717 --> 20:21.053
[SCOFFS] WHAT IS THIS,
A NERD BENEFIT?

20:21.136 --> 20:24.890
PRETTY, PRETTY PRINCESSES,
YOU'RE ON.

20:24.973 --> 20:26.266
SHOWTIME, LET'S GO, LADIES.

20:28.477 --> 20:30.354
[CHEERING]

20:32.731 --> 20:34.942
HELLO, SAN FRANCISCO.

20:35.025 --> 20:37.277
BOW DOWN TO THE PRINCESSES.

20:37.361 --> 20:38.862
[CHEERING]

20:38.946 --> 20:39.947
[GRUNTS]

20:40.030 --> 20:41.573
COUNT US OFF, SPECIAL P.

20:44.409 --> 20:47.621
UH, ONE, TWO... TRIANGLE.

20:47.704 --> 20:50.165
HELP.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.375
[AUDIENCE AND BESSIE GASP]

20:51.458 --> 20:53.293
SORRY, ROCKS, BUT WHEN
A HONEYBEE TEARS A WING

20:53.377 --> 20:56.421
{\an1}HER FELLOW BEES MUST
HELP HER GLUE IT BACK ON.

20:56.505 --> 20:59.091
OR STAPLE IT
OR USE A SAFETY PIN.

20:59.174 --> 21:01.802
WE TOTALLY GET IT, B-DOG,
GO HELP YOUR FRIENDS.

21:01.885 --> 21:04.137
THAT'S COOL, WE TOTALLY GET IT.

21:04.221 --> 21:05.639
{\an3}YOU GOTTA DO WHAT
YOU GOTTA DO, YEAH, SURE.

21:05.722 --> 21:08.308
THANKS, YOU GUYS ARE THE BEST.

21:08.392 --> 21:11.144
THERE GOES THE LONGEST-LASTING
DRUMMER WE'VE EVER HAD.

21:11.228 --> 21:13.397
{\an3}[GRUNTS]

21:13.480 --> 21:16.108
HAVE NO FEAR, HONEYBEES,
FOR I AM YOUR GLUE.

21:16.191 --> 21:19.027
IT'S A METAPHOR, EVERYBODY.

21:29.246 --> 21:32.040
♪ I'M A PRETTY,
PRETTY PRINCESS ♪

21:32.124 --> 21:35.711
♪ IT'S A FULL-TIME GIG ♪

21:35.794 --> 21:37.045
♪ EVERYBODY WANTS TO
BE MY FRIEND ♪

21:37.129 --> 21:40.007
♪ AND IT KIND OF MAKES ME SICK ♪

21:40.090 --> 21:41.466
[GAGGING IN RHYTHM]

21:41.550 --> 21:43.260
{\an1}♪ WHEN I'M NOT
IN MY CANOPY BED ♪

21:43.343 --> 21:47.639
{\an1}♪ I'M FILLING WITH MY DIARY
WITH STICKERS ♪

21:47.723 --> 21:49.391
♪ MY MOM SCREAMS... ♪

21:49.474 --> 21:51.560
♪ "GET DOWN HERE, PORTIA!" ♪

21:51.643 --> 21:53.520
♪ AND I JUST SAY, "WHATEVER" ♪

21:53.603 --> 21:57.649
♪ 'CAUSE I'M RUNNING WITH
THE RAINBOW UNICORN ♪

21:57.733 --> 21:59.818
♪ DON'T YOU WISH YOU WERE ME? ♪

21:59.901 --> 22:01.945
♪ I'M RUNNING WITH
THE RAINBOW UNICORN ♪

22:02.029 --> 22:05.574
♪ I WANT EVERYONE TO SEE ♪

22:05.657 --> 22:10.037
Portia and Bessie: ♪ I'M RUNNING
WITH THE RAINBOW UNICORN ♪

22:10.120 --> 22:13.081
♪ DON'T YOU WISH YOU WERE ME? ♪

22:13.165 --> 22:15.751
♪ RUNNING WITH
THE RAINBOW UNICORN ♪

22:15.834 --> 22:18.795
♪ AND I WANT EVERYONE TO SEE ♪

22:18.879 --> 22:24.259
{\an5}♪ HEY, LOOK AT ME... ♪

22:18.879 --> 22:24.259
[CHEERING]

22:25.927 --> 22:27.888
THANK YOU,
SAN FRANCISCO, GOOD NIGHT!

22:27.971 --> 22:29.473
[CHEERING]

22:29.556 --> 22:31.641
WHOA... SO WHEN DO WE GO ON?

22:32.434 --> 22:37.189
[♪...]

23:12.766 --> 23:14.476
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
